pson</small> -->
		                                    <h1 class=3D"title1">
		                                        What Is ABV?		                   =
                 </h1>
		                                </div>
		                                <div class=3D"blogmain_action">
		                                	<a href=3D"http://eepurl.com/gK_v89" tar=
get=3D"_blank" class=3D"btn btn_minwid btn_yellow" title=3D"Share">Sign Up<=
/a>
		                                	<a href=3D"https://www.singgin.com/produ=
ct-category/gin" class=3D"btn btn_minwid btn_yellow_solid" title=3D"Shop No=
w">Shop Now</a>
		                                </div>
		                            </div>

		                            <p class=3D"p1"><strong><span class=3D"s1">Th=
ere=E2=80=99s a lot of technical jargon in the wonderful world of distilled=
 spirits, and one of the most commonly asked questions in our industry is =
=E2=80=9CWhat does ABV mean?=E2=80=9D</span></strong></p>
<p>Who doesn=E2=80=99t love a gin hamper? The perfect gifts for drinkers of=
 gin, our hampers rise to any occasion =E2=80=93 from birthdays to annivers=
aries, congratulations to new homes, Christmas or just to say thank you. <a=
 href=3D"https://www.singgin.com/product-category/hampers/">Discover our ra=
nge of luxury gin hampers here</a>.</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://www.singgin.com/product-category/hampers/"><picture f=
etchpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"aligncenter size-full wp-=
image-19685">
<source type=3D"image/webp" srcset=3D"https://www.singgin.com/wp-content/up=
loads/2023/03/LWGH-SQUARE.jpg.webp 1080w, https://www.singgin.com/wp-conten=
t/uploads/2023/03/LWGH-SQUARE-300x300.jpg.webp 300w, https://www.singgin.co=
m/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/LWGH-SQUARE-1024x1024.jpg.webp 1024w, https://=
www.singgin.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/LWGH-SQUARE-150x150.jpg.webp 150=
w, https://www.singgin.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/LWGH-SQUARE-768x768.j=
pg.webp 768w, https://www.singgin.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/LWGH-SQUAR=
E-600x600.jpg.webp 600w, https://www.singgin.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03=
/LWGH-SQUARE-100x100.jpg.webp 100w" sizes=3D"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 108=
0px">
<img fetchpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://www.singgin.c=
om/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/LWGH-SQUARE.jpg" alt=3D"Luxury hamper contain=
ing a range of foods, a large bottle of gin and sparkling wine" width=3D"10=
80" height=3D"1080">
</picture>
</a></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Most countries legally require that this=
 abbreviation is displayed on every alcoholic beverage, so it=E2=80=99s an =
important term to understand.</span></p>
<p>Let=E2=80=99s take a look at some of the more confusing terms in the alc=
ohol industry and break them down=E2=80=A6</p>
<h2 class=3D"p1" style=3D"text-align: center;"><span class=3D"s1">What does=
 ABV stand for?</span></h2>
<p class=3D"p3"><span class=3D"s1">ABV stands for Alcohol By Volume.</span>=
</p>
<h2 class=3D"p1" style=3D"text-align: center;"><span class=3D"s1">What does=
 ABV mean?</span></h2>
<p><img decoding=3D"async" class=3D"aligncenter size-full wp-image-11725" s=
rc=3D"https://www.singgin.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Featured-GT-Servin=
g.webp" alt=3D"Close up of a bartender making a gin and tonic" width=3D"120=
0" height=3D"630"></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">ABV, or alcohol by volume, is a measure =
of alcoholic strength. The amount of ethanol (alcohol) in a container is sh=
own as a percentage of the overall volume of the drink. The higher the perc=
entage, the stronger the alcohol. So, water has an alcoholic strength of 0%=
 ABV, while pure alcohol is 100% ABV.</span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">In more scientific terms, ABV is defined=
 as the number of millilitres (mL) of pure ethanol present in 100mL of solu=
tion at 20deg. This percentage is also used to calculate the amount of tax =
paid on the drink. </span></p>
<h2 class=3D"p1" style=3D"text-align: center;"><span class=3D"s1">Where to =
find the ABV of your drink</span></h2>
<p class=3D"p3"><span class=3D"s1">You can find<span class=3D"Apple-convert=
ed-space">&nbsp; </span>the ABV of any alcoholic drink on the label in most=
 countries. It will show a number, followed by the percentage sign. </span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"p3"><span class=3D"s1">Some labels use the abbreviation =E2=80=
=9Cvol=E2=80=9D instead of ABV. So, if the label on a bottle says 20 vol, i=
t means that the content contains 20% pure alcohol.</span></p>
<h2 class=3D"p1" style=3D"text-align: center;"><span class=3D"s1">What is t=
he difference between ABV and Proof?</span></h2>
<p><img decoding=3D"async" class=3D"aligncenter size-full wp-image-11926" s=
rc=3D"https://www.singgin.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Copper-Still.webp"=
 alt=3D"" width=3D"1200" height=3D"630"></p>
<p class=3D"p3"><span class=3D"s1">Just like ABV, alcohol proof is a measur=
e of the amount of ethanol (alcohol) in an alcoholic drink. The term was or=
iginally used in England and was equal to about 1.821 times the percentage =
alcohol by volume (ABV). This term is most commonly used these days in the =
United States, where alcohol proof is defined as twice the percentage of AB=
V.</span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">So in the USA, a gin with 40% ABV is 80 =
proof and one that is 45% ABV is 90 proof.</span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">The term comes from a century ago, when =
liquor was =E2=80=98proofed=E2=80=99 by adding gunpowder and lighting it on=
 fire. If it didn=E2=80=99t light, the alcohol content was deemed too weak.=
 If it burned yellow, it was too strong. But if it burned blue, the proof w=
as just right ( around 57%, or 114 proof).&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Even today, a =E2=80=98proof spirit=E2=
=80=99 is 100 proof (50 percent ABV) or higher.</span></p>
<p class=3D"p3"><span class=3D"s1">The UK now uses the ABV standard instead=
 of alcohol proof to measure the amount of alcohol in a beverage. We think =
it=E2=80=99s a bit more straightforward!</span></p>
<h2 class=3D"p1" style=3D"text-align: center;"><span class=3D"s1">Average A=
BV of different types of alcohol</span></h2>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Most spirits range from 35 =E2=80=93 45%=
 ABV.</span></p>
<p>Liqueurs tend to range from 15 =E2=80=93 30% ABV. They=E2=80=99re not as=
 strong as spirits because the base spirit is blended with sugary fruit syr=
ups and sweetened, which dilutes the alcohol.</p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Ales typically start at 3.5% ABV, but so=
me stronger lagers can have as much as 6 or 7% ABV.</span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Wine tends to range from 13% to 15%.</sp=
an></p>
<h2 class=3D"p1" style=3D"text-align: center;"><span class=3D"s1">Common AB=
V of gins</span></h2>
<p><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"aligncenter size-full =
wp-image-11927" src=3D"https://www.singgin.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/S=
tainless-Steel-Vessell.webp" alt=3D"" width=3D"1200" height=3D"630"></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">In the European Union, the minimum stren=
gth of gin is 37.5% ABV. In the USA, it=E2=80=99s 40.0% ABV.</span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">The ABV of <a href=3D"https://www.singgi=
n.com/shop/">Sing Gin</a> is 40%. Along with alcohol, <a href=3D"https://ww=
w.singgin.com/can-you-make-gin-from-grapes/">Sing Gin is made from grapes</=
a> for a silky smooth texture and taste, as well as a blend of seven hand c=
rushed <a href=3D"https://www.singgin.com/botanicals-in-gin/">gin botanical=
s</a>.</span></p>
<p><a href=3D"https://www.singgin.com/what-are-the-different-types-of-gin/"=
>Different types of gin</a> have different average ABVs. Most are around th=
e 40% mark, but there are some notable differences.</p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Fruit gin, or sloe gin has an alcohol co=
ntent between 15 and 30% ABV. The EU requires sloe gin to be a minimum of 2=
5%. </span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Flavoured gins tend to have an ABV betwe=
en 37.5% and 40%.</span></p>
<p>The strongest gins, Navy Strength style gins, can be up to 58% ABV.</p>
<p>You can learn more about <a href=3D"https://www.singgin.com/what-is-gin-=
made-from/">how gin is made</a> in our blog post on the topic.</p>
<h2 style=3D"text-align: center;">Where is the ABV standard used?</h2>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">The ABV standard is used worldwide, alth=
ough the USA uses the term =E2=80=98Proof=E2=80=99. </span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">In France, the term =E2=80=98degrees Gay=
-Lussac=E2=80=99 is used instead of ABV. This is thanks to the French chemi=
st Joseph Louis Gay-Loussac. </span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Gay-Lussac uses the value of 15deg for t=
emperates instead of 20deg, so the scale is different to ABV.</span></p>
<h2 style=3D"text-align: center;">What is ethanol?</h2>
<p><span class=3D"s1">Ethanol is the chemical compound that makes a drink a=
lcoholic. It is created by a process called fermentation =E2=80=93 when y</=
span><span class=3D"s1">east is used to break down the sugars in a liquid.<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">The yeast eats the sugars and create alc=
ohols (including ethanol), flavours (or =E2=80=98congeners=E2=80=99) and ca=
rbon dioxide (CO2). This creates a liquid that is typically around 10% ABV.=
</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"s1">Different foods provide the starting point for differ=
ent types of alcohol. Wine is made from the sugar in grapes, beer from the =
sugar in malted barley, cider from the sugar in apples.</span></p>
<p>Then there are distilled spirits, like vodka, gin, rum and whiskey. Spir=
its go through a distillation process, which removes the water from the eth=
anol to create a distilled spirit. These beverages usually contain between =
40 and 50% alcohol.</p>
<p>If you=E2=80=99re interested in the distilling process used to make gin,=
 read about what goes on at <a href=3D"https://www.singgin.com/distillery/"=
>our distillery</a>.</p>
<h2 class=3D"p1" style=3D"text-align: center;"><span class=3D"s1"><b>How to=
 calculate ABV?</b></span></h2>
<p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">You can measure ABV using the ABV calcul=
ator <a href=3D"https://flaviar.com/blog/measuring-alcohol-content" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">here</a>.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Did you learn something about ABV from this article? Feel free to share =
it with a friend or post it on social media!</p>
